API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /movements/:movementId
  - Response: { data: Movement | null, error?: string }
- GET /movements/:movementId/events
  - Query: page, pageSize, filters
  - Response: { data: NarrativeEvent[], page: number, pageSize: number, total: number }
- POST /movements/:movementId/export-audit
  - Body: { includeEvents: string[], includeCalculationInputs: boolean }
  - Response: { artifactUrlJson: string, artifactUrlPdf: string, artifactId: string }
- Optional: GET /movements/:movementId/export-status for long-running jobs

Security: [Authentication, authorization requirements]
- Ensure user is authenticated via existing session/token (JWT or session cookie) for page access.
- Authorization: User must have read access to the company and movement data; ensure role-based access if needed.
- Audit export endpoints should require elevated permissions if artifacts contain sensitive data; sign artifacts server-side and provide verifiable signatures.

Validation: [Input validation rules]
- Filters: Validate date ranges to ensure start <= end; sanitize inputs to prevent injection in query parameters.
- Movement and event IDs: Validate UUID-like or slugs format; guard against undefined IDs.
- API responses: Use Array.isArray for lists; default to [] for null data; ensure essential fields exist before rendering.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Drilldown page renders without crashes when movement has 0 events; the UI shows empty state but all sections render gracefully.
- [ ] NarrativeEventsTable uses safe (events ?? []).map(...) and displays all fields with proper null checks; the “view raw” button opens RawPayloadModal with payload data.
- [ ] RawPayloadModal loads provenance metadata and offers a download of the raw payload JSON; handles absent payload gracefully.
- [ ] TimelineReplay can advance through the events, highlighting the current event and marking repetitions/spikes; keyboard navigation supported.
- [ ] FiltersPanel correctly filters events by source type, authority tier, credibility flags, and date range; Apply refreshes the list and timeline.
- [ ] Audit Export button triggers server-side artifact generation; downloads for JSON and PDF are offered; artifact includes movement metadata, filtered events, weighting parameters, and calculation inputs.
- [ ] Back to Company View link returns to the Company View with preserved context (companyId and current window) and no data leakage.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system and ensure the page conforms to the Visual Style and Design Philosophy described earlier:
- Use the exact color palette tokens, typography scales, spacing guidelines, and component treatments.
- Maintain hierarchical clarity: Narrative Header at top, followed by the Events list, Raw Payload modal as needed, then the Timeline and Filters, with the Audit Export controls clearly visible.
- Ensure consistent card design, subtle borders, soft shadows, and accessible controls.
- Implement micro-interactions with the described timings (150–220ms hover, 300ms panel transitions) for a polished enterprise feel.

Visual Style
[Reconfirm the styling constraints from the Visual Style section in the prompt; ensure all components adhere to the tokenized palette and typography rules.]

Connected Pages
- Company View (IPI Detail): Shows the selected company's current IPI, directional change, top 3 contributing narratives, timeline, and CTA to drill down to 'Why did this move?'.

Connected Features
- Drilldown & Traceability UI: Interactive UI to inspect narratives, list underlying NarrativeEvents, view raw payloads, replay timelines, and export audit artifacts.
- Audit Export & Artifact Generation: Generate signed, exportable audit artifacts (JSON + PDF) including raw payload references, event lists, weighting parameters, and calculation inputs used for a given IPI view.

